<!doctype html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><title>AI Show Integrity Review | Universal Orlando</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css"></head><body class="document-body"><nav class="document-nav no-print"><a class="nav-name" href="index.html">Russell Dudek <span>/ Candidate Vision</span></a><div class="doc-actions"><a class="btn primary" href="docs/Russell-Dudek-Universal-Orlando-AI-Show-Integrity-Review.pdf" download>Download PDF</a><button class="btn" onclick="window.print()">Print</button></div></nav><main class="document-shell"><section class="report-page report-title"><div class="report-inner"><div class="report-lockup"><img src="assets/brand/universal-orlando-logo.png" alt="Universal Orlando Resort"><span class="report-label">Independent candidate brief by Russell Dudek</span></div><h1>AI Show Integrity Review</h1><p class="deck">A production-readiness and operating-evidence worksheet for consequential AI services.</p><div class="thesis">Use before release, after a material change and after a meaningful operating event.</div><footer class="page-footer"><span>Russell Dudek | AI Show Integrity Review</span><span>1</span></footer></div></section>
<section class="report-page"><div class="report-inner"><header class="report-header"><h1>01 | Define the scene and cue</h1><img src="assets/brand/universal-orlando-logo.png" alt="Universal Orlando Resort"></header><section class="report-section"><div class="review-grid"><div class="review-field"><strong>Service / workflow</strong><span>What exact moment is changing?</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Operating owner</strong><span>Who owns the outcome after launch?</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Guest or business outcome</strong><span>What improves, for whom and why now?</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Baseline and value hypothesis</strong><span>Current performance and expected movement.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Workflow and adoption burden</strong><span>What must people do differently?</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Consequence tier</strong><span>Low / moderate / high / critical; rationale.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Data context</strong><span>Sources, lineage, quality, timeliness, access and privacy.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Model role and limits</strong><span>Recommend, classify, generate, optimize, automate or assist.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Human authority</strong><span>Approve, override, escalate and stop rights.</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div><div class="review-field"><strong>Prohibited behavior</strong><span>What must the system never do?</span><div class="worksheet-line"></div></div></div><h2>Scene/Cue finding</h2><div class="review-field" style="min-height:1.15in"><strong>What must be corrected before technical release review?</strong></div></section><footer class="page-footer"><span>Russell Dudek | AI Show Integrity Review</span><span>2</span></footer></div></section>
